1
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,440
There are two forks ahead.

2
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:38,840
One leads to Suzhou.

3
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:41,240
Last time, Your Excellency took this route.

4
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:42,720
Though the road is a bit winding,

5
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:43,720
it’s mostly main roads.

6
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:45,200
The other leads to Jingzhou.

7
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,880
We could exit via Jingzhou today.

8
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:49,000
But the side roads are more winding.

9
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,280
Young Master,

10
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:55,400
in my experience,

11
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,400
entering through Suzhou is better.

12
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:59,360
Last time I returned to Ling An,

13
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,320
I found a road

14
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,560
that’s not on the map.

15
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,320
Go ask Yu’er about it later.

16
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:04,880
If she agrees,

17
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,120
I’ll lead the way.

18
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,200
Yes.

19
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,040
Madam—

20
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,880
Oh, no, Young Master Nan.

21
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,040
You—

22
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,120
You called me that so suddenly,

23
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,520
it feels a bit awkward.

24
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,320
Then I’ll—

25
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,560
You may leave now.

26
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,480
Yes, Your Excellency.

27
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,800
Are you upset?

28
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,240
No.

29
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,040
There’s nothing between me
and that little princess.

30
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,360
Really, nothing at all.

31
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:47,960
I know.

32
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,600
I’m just a bit tired.

33
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,320
Don’t overthink it.

34
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,080
I’m glad you care
about my feelings.

35
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,120
It makes me happy.

36
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:03,160
Then I should definitely—

37
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,520
Your subordinate has a report.

38
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:09,240
What is it?

39
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:11,720
We planned to take
the previous route.

40
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,080
But Second Young Master Rui said

41
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,240
he knows a side road

42
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,560
and suggests we exit
via Suzhou this time.

43
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,840
Second Brother is more familiar
with travel between the two states.

44
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:20,080
He knows it better.

45
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,760
If he’s more confident,

46
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,080
let him lead the way.

47
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,560
Is everything packed?

48
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:27,720
We’re ready to depart anytime.

49
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:29,080
Then we’ll leave in a moment.

50
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:29,880
Yes.

51
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:33,120
Gather up!

52
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,520
Route change!

53
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,840
We’ll travel side roads
through Suzhou.

54
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,480
Chongming Guard, stand by.

55
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,680
Guard the carriage at all times.

56
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,440
No mistakes allowed.

57
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:41,280
Is that clear?

58
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,240
Understood!

59
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,720
You’re up early today.

60
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,120
I don’t want to go
to Pingxiang anymore.

61
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:46,960
Take me back.

62
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,320
Sure.

63
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:56,080
I mean, I want
to return to Ling An.

64
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:57,920
I heard you.

65
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:59,320
If you want to go back,
we’ll go back.

66
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,000
You—

67
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,040
You don’t object?

68
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,120
You’re a princess.

69
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:04,680
As long as you cover for us,

70
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,480
whatever you order,

71
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,560
we’ll just do it.

72
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:07,720
Alright.

73
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,720
Then go tell them now.

74
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:10,560
Send me back.

75
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,760
I’m just a commoner.

76
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,880
I can’t order those big shots around.

77
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:19,640
Princess, you’d better
tell Yu’er yourself.

78
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,360
Just tell her you want
to return to Ling An.

79
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,960
And want a marriage alliance
with Qian Yuan.

80
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:26,480
You’re Your Majesty’s
own sister anyway.

81
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,280
Your Majesty will
find a way for you.

82
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:29,880
If this doesn’t work,

83
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:32,480
we’ll think of a second
or third plan.

84
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:34,680
Someone will always
find a way for you.

85
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:35,720
I—

86
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,640
I’m not as willful
as you say.

87
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,360
Alright.

88
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,560
I was just impulsive earlier.

89
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,640
Can’t you comfort me a little?

90
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:06,560
Princess,

91
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:08,800
Liking someone is your own business.

92
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:11,400
But you can’t expect
the same in return.

93
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:12,880
Of course.

94
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,400
If you want to use your title
to force marriage,

95
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,960
then forget what I said.

96
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:22,040
But you don’t seem
the type to do that.

97
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,480
Otherwise,

98
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,600
you wouldn’t have chased
Yu’er for so many years.

99
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:30,680
You talk like you know me well.

100
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:35,360
Aren’t all princesses
in storybooks like this?

101
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,280
Beautiful and kind-hearted,

102
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,200
just sharp-tongued.

103
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:47,080
So what should I do

104
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,760
for them to like me?

105
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,720
Why do you have to become

106
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,960
what they like?

107
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,800
Someone will like
the real you.

108
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,200
Who is it?

109
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,000
Maybe they haven’t
shown up yet.

110
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,800
But believe that
such a person exists.

111
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:09,960
He’ll like you,

112
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,400
respect you, understand you,

113
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,600
and accept everything about you.

114
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:16,600
And you’ll do the same
because you like him.

115
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:18,560
You’ll do all that for him.

116
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,640
Because of love,

117
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:25,680
you’ll respect, accept,
and understand him.

118
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,280
I don’t fully understand,

119
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,680
but I’ll try.

120
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:35,360
Thank you for telling me this.

121
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,440
Let’s go, it’s time to leave.

122
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,560
Master

123
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,200
Master

124
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,680
Master

125
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:07,840
Pretending not to hear again

126
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,120
Master

127
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,320
I'm here

128
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,480
You scared me to death

129
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,240
I'm fishing

130
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,440
Don't scare the fish away

131
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,040
You didn't even bait the hook

132
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,440
You won't catch anything even if I don't call you

133
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,600
This is called "the willing fish bites"

134
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:26,960
Whether it bites or not

135
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,760
It's up to the fish

136
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,480
Come on

137
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:32,480
There aren't any fish in this pond

138
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,120
You're just mooching off the old man's fish

139
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:37,760
Master

140
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,760
Can you stop fishing for now

141
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:40,520
What for

142
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,880
I brought a friend

143
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:44,680
I want you to write a prescription for him

144
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,400
His mother's illness is similar to Lady Nan's

145
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:50,440
I hope you can prescribe something

146
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,120
She's not here

147
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,600
I haven't checked her pulse

148
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,640
How can I prescribe anything

149
00:07:57,960 --> 00:08:00,120
His mother is sick and can't come

150
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,600
Didn't I describe Lady Nan's pulse to you too

151
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,680
Just let him describe it

152
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,360
I'm fishing

153
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,400
Seriously

154
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,880
Do you want grilled fish

155
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,080
Sure

156
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,600
I'll borrow some fish from next door

157
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:18,520
Wait for me

158
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,240
Greetings, sir

159
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,160
Young friend

160
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,040
Came uninvited

161
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:33,120
That's not very polite

162
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,040
I didn't mean to intrude

163
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,520
My mother's illness is urgent

164
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,400
I hope you can forgive me

165
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,680
What's your mother's name

166
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,880
I never treat those without a name

167
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:51,880
I can't reveal her name right now

168
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,520
If you can't say

169
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:56,880
Then I can't treat her

170
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:57,800
Sir

171
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,400
Please, sir

172
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:03,800
I hope you'll reconsider

173
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:45,240
We'll reach Suzhou soon

174
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,400
How much longer to pass the checkpoint

175
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,840
If we don't rest

176
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:52,280
We'll reach Pingxiang before dark

177
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,080
Princess

178
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:58,080
Should we rest in Suzhou tonight

179
00:09:58,680 --> 00:09:59,360
I'm not tired

180
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:01,520
Brother Chenxiao and the others are the ones working hard

181
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:02,680
Brother Chenxiao

182
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:05,360
Should we stay in Suzhou tonight

183
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,680
Let's head to Pingxiang as soon as possible

184
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:09,800
Once we're there

185
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,120
We can stay at the post station

186
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,000
Is that okay, Yu'er

187
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:13,680
I'm fine with anything

188
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,280
Alright

189
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,520
Let's do as Brother Chenxiao says

190
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,280
Let's keep going

191
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,720
Still haven't caught any, right

192
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:58,800
The old man next door caught lots of yellow croaker

193
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,960
We can have fried fish for lunch today

194
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:05,840
What's wrong

195
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:08,000
Seems like it went wrong

196
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:11,000
The old man wouldn't give you a prescription, huh

197
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,040
It's fine

198
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:13,800
Let's just treat this as a trip to relax

199
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,240
I'll help you eat all his food later

200
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,160
And drink all his wine

201
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:17,520
No

202
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,840
I was too rash

203
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:25,800
You

204
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,120
You can't catch any fish anyway

205
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:30,040
Why not help me tidy up the kitchen

206
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,280
And prepare some side dishes

207
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:47,920
You annoy your master like this

208
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,160
He won't get mad, will he

209
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:51,600
My master is just stubborn

210
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,920
That's why I told you

211
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,520
You need at least half a month

212
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,840
Who knows when he'll change his mind

213
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:57,720
And refuse to treat you

214
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,360
Stay with me for a while

215
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,040
Spend more time here

216
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:01,280
He'll calm down eventually

217
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:02,840
You're right

218
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,360
Sincerity works wonders

219
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:12,480
Let's catch a few more fish by the river

220
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:13,520
And pick some vegetables too

221
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:14,520
Okay

222
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,600
Should we add another layer

223
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:27,720
Brother Chenxiao

224
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:28,720
Let's go out and play

225
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,280
Alright

226
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:35,840
I'm a bit tired today

227
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:37,800
Let Second Brother go instead

228
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,360
Enough

229
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:42,480
Can't you see the two brothers have things to discuss

230
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,000
Let's go

231
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,160
I'll go play with you

232
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:45,720
What do you need to discuss

233
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:48,160
Is there something you can't tell me

234
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,480
Princess, lately

235
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:52,720
Don't call Chenxiao by name for now

236
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,840
There are too many eyes in Pingxiang

237
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,280
We should be careful

238
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,160
Then what should I call him

239
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:02,600
He's the head guard now

240
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,600
You all

241
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:05,120
Shouldn't get too close either

242
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:08,680
Alright

243
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,840
For the head guard's safety

244
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:11,840
I'll be careful

245
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:16,320
Wicked fox

246
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,680
Do you know how to play cuju

247
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:19,960
Just for fun

248
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,280
Fishing and cuju

249
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,720
If it's for amusement

250
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,040
There's nothing I can't do

251
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:24,480
Let's go

252
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:25,600
Teach me cuju

253
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:29,160
There are people watching us everywhere now

254
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:31,840
So

255
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,480
Let's play this instead

256
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:34,840
Take this

257
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:35,920
What is this

258
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,400
Can you eat this

259
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:41,240
No, no, that's not for eating

260
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,040
I'll make it for you

261
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,600
Watch closely

262
00:13:58,840 --> 00:13:59,480
Take it

263
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,840
Master, why are you like this

264
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,360
I caught a few more fish for you

265
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,480
I'll stew them for you at lunch, isn't that enough

266
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,840
Give me back my fishing rod

267
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:13,280
Go wherever you want

268
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:14,600
You

269
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:36,680
Miss Qiao, you're climbing the wall again

270
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,600
You think this little thing can stop me

271
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:52,960
Not using the main entrance,

272
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:54,680
must mean you're all thieves.

273
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:57,400
Sorry to trouble you, sir.

274
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,840
You know it's a bother, yet you still come?

275
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:01,680
Go, go, go.

276
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:02,680
You've been tired all day.

277
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:03,480
Take a break first.

278
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,720
Who let you in here?

279
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,840
You can't stay here.

280
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,400
There's a side room my father and I built.

281
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:14,960
He'll stay there.

282
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,920
We don't need your permission.

283
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,360
Doesn't matter who built it.

284
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:19,680
You simply can't live here.

285
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,720
Then go talk to my father.

286
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:24,920
Fine.

287
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:25,840
Alright.

288
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,240
You're here.

289
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,360
